metadata.name: لَّآ إِلَٰهَ إِلَّآ أَنتَ سُبْحَٰنَكَ إِنِّى كُنتُ مِنَ ٱلظَّٰلِمِينَ #1/3
metadata.description:
A series of works depicting Biblical stories and historical figures in paper-cut format. 
This scene depicts Jonah about to be swallowed by a whale. Ordered to go to Nineveh to preach, Jonah abandoned the mission and set sail in the opposite direction. The three days and three nights in the whale's belly was the equivalent of his 'time-out'.
